Diagnosis . Females of
Cheiramiona hogsbackensis
sp . nov .
can be differentiated by the wide curved shape of the epigynal depression (
Fig. 17
) and the copulatory tubes that proceed directly posteriorly from the SPER (
Fig. 18
); males are promptly recognized by the denticles on the inner margin of the RTA (
Figs 20–21
).

Distribution . Only known from the type locality (
Fig. 98
).
